## Project info
GENSYMCID-1847 - Regression test for GENSYMCID-1797
Quote from GENSYMCID-1797 Release Notes:
<<Basically, on "getting", there is re-use if the same object is (again) getting the connection. If reuse was indeed, well, used, then the `current-utilization` count would not be incremented. But, on "releasing", this was not taken into account, but `current-utilization` was blindly decremented. >>
Our solution is based upon test kb attached to GENSYMCID-1797. Refer to GENSYMCID-1797 Release Notes for futher details.
## Code changes
Most important change to test kb from GENSYMCID-1797 is that we made use of src/scripts/StartODBC.bat . For this we needed to change TEST-DATABASE-INTERFACE-INSTANCE attributes.
Note -shutdown_on_disconnect parameter which is intended to avoid leaving running g2-odbc.exe instances in case of G2 abort. Also we had to change StartODBC.bat and src/tests/build.xml to make it work.
Another change is that we deliver kb in XML format. It also required a change to src/tests/build.xml
## Known issues
-shutdown_on_disconnect fails to terminate g2-odbc.exe if connection was not yet established.
